com.tymeac.base

Class AreaThreadsAnchor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tymeac.base.AreaThreadsAnchor

  • public final class AreaThreadsAnchor
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the anchor point for the Queue's thread Classes. The anchor contains the methods for iterating over the thread management objects in the pool. The pool is simply an ArrayList of AreaThreadMgmt objects. The Queue structure: level one -- AreaBase level two -- this level three -- AreaThreadMgmt (the individual thread)

      • setShutdown

        protected int setShutdown(int nbr_async)
        The system is shutting down. Inform all the normal threads to exit. Output Agent threads are ignored unless there are no async requests working, then they are terminated if alive. Other then with a cancelled status there is a chance of error since the status is set() rather than atomically set with a CAS. Since the system is shutting down, this is acceptable.
        Parameters:
        nbr_async - int - number of async requests busy
        Returns:
        int
